## Feature 4 Complete: SFT Loss Masking

### Files Created
- src/training/__init__.py — empty package marker
- src/training/sft_trainer.py — implements apply_loss_mask() and IGNORE_INDEX
- tests/training/__init__.py — empty package marker
- tests/training/test_masking.py — 4 tests for loss masking behavior

### Implementation Summary
apply_loss_mask(input_ids, labels, tokenizer, mask_role='user') -> list[int]:
- Reads tokenizer.role_start_ids: dict[str, list[int]] to find turn boundaries
- Scans input_ids for each role's marker token sequence using _find_subsequence()
- Sets all non-assistant segment positions to IGNORE_INDEX (-100)
- Raises ValueError if no assistant turn is found
- Returns a new list (immutable — does not mutate input labels)

### Tests (all pass)
- test_user_tokens_masked: user segment positions == -100
- test_assistant_tokens_unmasked: assistant segment labels unchanged
- test_system_tokens_masked: system segment positions == -100
- test_all_masked_raises: ValueError when no assistant marker in input_ids

